The Chompret criteria for a diagnosis of Li-Fraumeni Syndrome (LFS) include: 
1. One first-degree relative with a diagnosis of sarcoma, glioma, or breast cancer before the age of 45; 
2. A family history of two or more first- or second-degree relatives with sarcoma, glioma, breast, or adrenocortical carcinoma; 
3. One first- or second-degree relative with two or more primary cancers; and 
4. A family history of two or more first- or second-degree relatives with any combination of breast, central nervous system (CNS), soft tissue, or adrenocortical cancer.
